{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-27T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"This is the kind of landscape that makes maps feel suddenly more interesting. Evening settles quietly over Maligne Lake in Jasper National Park, Alberta. As temperatures drop, the surface stills, mirroring snow-dusted peaks that formed during the last Ice Age. Stretching about 22 kilometres, the lake owes its existence to glacial movement that carved the valley and left behind meltwater basins. Today, cold, oxygen-rich freshwater sustains ecosystems that include species such as lake trout and mountain whitefish. Boat cruises and paddling routes offer one of the best ways to view Spirit Island, the small but widely photographed landmark featured in the image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Aurora over Spirit Island on Maligne Lake, Jasper National Park, Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© Mumemories/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maligne+Lake+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260327_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland"},"Ssd":"20260327","Name":"AuroraIsland","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4443502358","FullDateString":"2026 3월 27"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Running along the remote southwest coast of Vancouver Island, the West Coast Trail is one of the country's most legendary hikes. Located in British Columbia's Pacific Rim National Park Reserve, the trail stretches about 76 kilometres through rainforest, beaches and rocky shoreline. It was established in 1907 as a lifesaving route for shipwreck survivors along what sailors once called the 'Graveyard of the Pacific.'","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Logan Creek Suspension Bridge, West Coast Trail, British Columbia, Canada","Copyright":"© Tandem Stock/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=West+Coast+Trail+hike&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260326_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek"},"Ssd":"20260326","Name":"LoganCreek","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8107496948","FullDateString":"2026 3월 26"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Manatees may seem slow and sleepy, but they have some surprising tricks under the surface. For starters, they are one of the few mammals that constantly replace their teeth. As old molars wear down from chewing gritty seagrass, new ones slowly roll forward like a conveyor belt—handy for an animal that eats for up to eight hours a day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Juvenile manatees in a freshwater spring, Crystal River, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Gregory Sweeney/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Manatee&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260325_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring"},"Ssd":"20260325","Name":"ManateeSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7760366755","FullDateString":"2026 3월 25"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When mist drifts across Königssee Lake, located in Bavaria, Germany, in the early morning, the landscape feels almost timeless. The long, narrow mountain lake lies in south-eastern Bavaria, cradled between the steep rock faces of the Berchtesgaden Alps. Large parts of the lake lie within Berchtesgaden National Park, Germany's only Alpine national park, where nature is largely allowed to develop without human interference.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Königssee Lake, Bavaria, Germany","Copyright":"© EyeEm Mobile GmbH/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Konigssee+Lake+Bavaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260324_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog"},"Ssd":"20260324","Name":"KoenigsseeFog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4902303534","FullDateString":"2026 3월 24"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The strength of nature is nowhere more evident than in powerful storms. Scary? Yes. Fascinating? Even more so. Learning to understand and respect these forces is how people learn to live alongside them. The image of lightning over saguaro cacti captures that balance perfectly. The Sonoran Desert, spanning 260,000 square kilometres across the United States and Mexico, may appear dry and still, but it hosts one of North America's most dynamic desert climates.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lightning storm over saguaro cacti, Sonoran Desert, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Jack Dykinga/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sonoran+Desert+Arizona&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260323_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm"},"Ssd":"20260323","Name":"SonoranStorm","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5466478182","FullDateString":"2026 3월 23"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water has always shaped human survival, but moments come when simply flowing along is no longer enough—we have to protect the systems that carry us forward. Few places capture that urgency like Lake Tanganyika, set deep within the Great Rift Valley of eastern Africa. Seen from space, it stretches like a narrow ribbon about 676 kilometres long, linking Tanzania, Burundi, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia. At the shoreline, it's a 10-million-year-old rift basin, formed as the Earth's crust slowly pulled apart.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_ROW4763595612_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_ROW4763595612_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lake Tanganyika, Africa","Copyright":"© BEST-BACKGROUNDS/NASA/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lake+Tanganyika&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260322_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater"},"Ssd":"20260322","Name":"TanganyikaWater","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4763595612","FullDateString":"2026 3월 22"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If Earth ran on routine check-ups, wetlands like the Danube Delta, shared between Romania and Ukraine, would top the list. This vast landscape quietly filters water, absorbs floodwaters and shelters wildlife on a remarkable scale. Covering more than 5,800 square kilometres, the Danube Delta Biosphere Reserve is one of Europe's largest and best-preserved wetlands. It's where the Danube River finally slows down, splitting into channels, lakes, reed beds and marshes before meeting the Black Sea. Letea Forest, featured in today's image, is a part of this vast biosphere.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_ROW4397618654_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_ROW4397618654_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Letea Forest, Danube Delta, Romania","Copyright":"© Wild Wonders of Europe/Widstrand/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Danube+Delta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260321_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest"},"Ssd":"20260321","Name":"LeteaForest","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4397618654","FullDateString":"2026 3월 21"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Some bridges in Amsterdam just get you across a canal. The Armbrug does more—it seems to wave hello as you pass. Nestled over the Oudezijds Voorburgwal canal, its name, meaning 'arm bridge,' refers to the nearby Oudezijds Armsteeg (Old Side Arm Alley), not a literal limb, but it's easy to imagine it greeting cyclists and pedestrians along the way.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_ROW0384861076_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_ROW0384861076_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Armbrug bridge, Amsterdam, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Alexander Spatari/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Armbrug+bridge+Amsterdam&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260403_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge"},"Ssd":"20260403","Name":"ArmbrugBridge","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0384861076","FullDateString":"2026 4월 3"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring announces itself across California's Central Valley with the first bursts of wildflowers following the winter rains. Stretching about 720 kilometres from north to south and covering approximately 51,800 square kilometres, the valley is one of the world's most productive agricultural regions. In early spring, however, an older identity briefly resurfaces. From March through April, native annuals such as goldfields, tidy tips and owl's clover quickly germinate once temperature and soil moisture are optimal. They race to complete their life cycles before the long dry season begins.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WildflowerValley_ROW2763453477_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WildflowerValley_ROW2763453477_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Wildflower bloom, Central Valley, California, United States","Copyright":"© Jeff Lewis/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260402_WildflowerValley\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Central+Valley+California&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260402_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260402_WildflowerValley"},"Ssd":"20260402","Name":"WildflowerValley","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2763453477","FullDateString":"2026 4월 2"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, let's hop into the world of one of nature's smallest yet most hardworking ambassadors. Frogs may not wear crowns—unless you believe in Frog Kings—but they do rule quietly behind the scenes. By keeping insect populations in check, they help ecosystems stay balanced. Even more impressive? Their sensitive skin also means they react quickly to changes in their surroundings, which is why scientists often look at frogs to understand the health of wetlands and forests. Talk about living barometers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.JapaneseTreeFrog_ROW2089186925_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.JapaneseTreeFrog_ROW2089186925_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Japanese tree frog in a pink morning glory","Copyright":"© Tetsuya Tanooka/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260401_JapaneseTreeFrog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Japanese+tree+frog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260401_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260401_JapaneseTreeFrog"},"Ssd":"20260401","Name":"JapaneseTreeFrog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2089186925","FullDateString":"2026 4월 1"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Paradise Cave makes a powerful first impression the moment visitors step inside. This vast limestone cavern lies deep within Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park in central Vietnam, a region marked by rugged mountains and countless hidden caves. Stretching 31 kilometres, Paradise Cave is one of Asia's longest dry caves, and its scale is immediately apparent. High ceilings rise above the walkways and layered patterns formed by mineral-rich water over millions of years line the walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ParadiseCave_ROW1547496612_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ParadiseCave_ROW1547496612_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Paradise Cave, Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park, Vietnam","Copyright":"© Pakawat Thongcharoen/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260331_ParadiseCave\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Paradise+Cave+Vietnam&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260331_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260331_ParadiseCave"},"Ssd":"20260331","Name":"ParadiseCave","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1547496612","FullDateString":"2026 3월 31"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The demoiselle crane is a small yet striking migratory bird found across Central Asia, from its breeding grounds in the steppes of Kazakhstan, Mongolia and northern China, to its wintering grounds in India, Nepal and parts of Africa. With its elegant appearance—slender neck, long legs and beautiful plumage—it is often considered one of the most graceful crane species. They are known for their intricate courtship dances, during which pairs engage in synchronized movements and calls, creating a beautiful spectacle.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.IndiaCranes_ROW8052837107_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.IndiaCranes_ROW8052837107_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Demoiselle cranes, India","Copyright":"© Axel Gomille/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260330_IndiaCranes\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Demoiselle+cranes&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260330_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260330_IndiaCranes"},"Ssd":"20260330","Name":"IndiaCranes","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8052837107","FullDateString":"2026 3월 30"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Peggy's Cove is a small yet captivating village on the rugged coast of Nova Scotia that offers a glimpse of life by the sea. The village's most famous landmark is Peggy's Point Lighthouse—also known as Peggy's Cove Lighthouse—first established in 1868 and replaced by the current structure in 1915. For over a century, it has guided ships through the ever-changing Atlantic waters, serving as a timeless symbol of coastal life. The surrounding landscape, with its windswept beauty and crashing waves, feels almost untouched by time.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Peggy's Point Lighthouse, Atlantic Coast, Nova Scotia, Canada","Copyright":"© Prashanth Bala/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Peggys+Point+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260329_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse"},"Ssd":"20260329","Name":"PeggysLighthouse","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0925207018","FullDateString":"2026 3월 29"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The African buffalo, a powerful and imposing creature, roams the savannas and wetlands of Tanzania, particularly within the Ngorongoro Conservation Area (NCA). Known for their large, curved horns and massive size, they are one of Africa's 'Big Five' (buffalo, elephant, leopard, rhino, lion) and are widely respected for their strength and resilience. The NCA, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, offers a dramatic and ecologically rich setting for observing these formidable herbivores.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"African buffalo, Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania","Copyright":"© jesuss8/500px/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=African+buffalo&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260328_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo"},"Ssd":"20260328","Name":"CapeBuffalo","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0708366233","FullDateString":"2026 3월 28"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"오늘의 이미지","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"자세히","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"기부하기","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"토막 정보:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"최근 홈페이지 이미지","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"{0}의 홈페이지 이미지","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"역사 속 이날","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"{0} 이 날짜에, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"오늘의 Bing 홈 페이지 공유","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"이미지를 다운로드하세요. 이 이미지는 바탕 화면에만 사용하도록 제한됩니다.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"이 이미지 다운로드","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"이 이미지는 바탕화면으로 다운로드할 수 없습니다.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"정보","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK":"https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2127455","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK_TEXT":"Bing 배경 화면 앱 다운로드","LOC_BING_APP_TEXT":"장치에서 Bing 배경 화면 받기","LOC_BING_APP_LINK_PC":"https://bing.microsoftapp.net/bing/?adjust=nk9xri2_dzfz5n2","LOC_BING_APP_LINK_MOBILE":"https://app.adjust.com/d93ddtl_a75k0gg?deeplink=